        "title": "fix(googlechat): preserve thread targets through reply delivery",
        "body": "## Summary\n- Repair Google Chat reply delivery so text chunks, media sends, typing-message fallback, and durable final delivery use the intended current thread target without leaking stale reply metadata.\n- Keep `replyToMode` semantics intact for implicit vs explicit reply targets.\n- Carry forward the useful prior work from #74235 and the earlier #43112/#67055 thread-routing attempts.\n\n## Verification\n- `node scripts/run-vitest.mjs extensions/googlechat/src/monitor.reply-delivery.test.ts extensions/googlechat/src/monitor-durable.test.ts`\n- `pnpm check:changed`\n\nRefs: #42510, #69422, #70041, #74235.\n\nClawSweeper 🐠 replacement reef notes:\n- Cluster: gitcrawl-4952-google-chat-dm-threading-broken-each-response-creates-new-thread\n- Source PRs: https://github.com/openclaw/openclaw/pull/74235, https://github.com/openclaw/openclaw/pull/67055, https://github.com/openclaw/openclaw/pull/43112, https://github.com/openclaw/openclaw/pull/30965\n- Credit: Preserve source PR attribution for https://github.com/openclaw/openclaw/pull/74235 after live hydration identifies its author and branch writability.; Credit @banddude for the prior replyToMode/off-mode attempt in https://github.com/openclaw/openclaw/pull/67055 when release-note context mentions provenance.; Credit @neeravmakwana for the earlier replyToMode/thread-routing attempt in https://github.com/openclaw/openclaw/pull/43112 when release-note context mentions provenance.; Credit @novan for the landed Google Chat messageReplyOption groundwork in https://github.com/openclaw/openclaw/pull/30965 if the final PR body discusses the regression history.\n- Validation: node scripts/run-vitest.mjs extensions/googlechat/src/monitor.reply-delivery.test.ts extensions/googlechat/src/monitor-durable.test.ts; pnpm check:changed\n- Replacement reason: ClawSweeper could not update the source PR branch directly, so it opened a writable replacement PR instead.\n\nInherited issue-closing references from the source PR:\nFixes #52475\nCloses #42510\n\nCo-author credit kept:\n- @jai: Co-authored-by: Jai Govindani <1943284+jai@users.noreply.github.com>\n- @banddude: Co-authored-by: banddude <127166397+banddude@users.noreply.github.com>\n- @neeravmakwana: Co-authored-by: Neerav Makwana <261249544+neeravmakwana@users.noreply.github.com>\n- @novan: Co-authored-by: Novan Adrian <316959+novan@users.noreply.github.com>\n\nfish notes: model gpt-5.5, reasoning high; reviewed against 93362401da0f.\n",
